 Jeffreys Bay - Coronavirus (COVID-19) community screening will kick off across Kouga this week as part of collective government efforts to stop the spread of the pandemic. "The screening will be conducted door-to-door in communities by local clinic staff," described Laura-Leigh Randall, Kouga Municipality Media Liaison Officer. She said that the following areas will be targeted this week (6 - 10 April): "The screening forms part of the national mass community screening programme that is currently being implemented across South Africa," Randall said. "So far, 5 400 fieldworkers have been trained and deployed to various areas." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 